Major #1 Name: Biomedical Engineering

Short Summary: Biomedical Engineering lies in physical and life sciences, incorporating principles from physics and chemistry to understand the operation of living systems. An education in Biomedical Engineering enables students to translate abstract hypothesis and scientific knowledge into working systems (e.g., prosthetic devices and imaging systems).

Info about Test:
This test will question you on your personality to see what major and what college is best for how you are. Consider what you are like so you get the results that you desire the most. Take your time to think about what people think about you.
1) What kind of job fields are you interested in?
2) How do you describe yourself?
3) What type of career are you considering for yourself?
4) Do you want to be able to challenge yourself?
5) What is your current income level for tuition costs
6) What size college would you consider?
